The paper presents a neural network architecture for non-linear dimensionality reduction and object recognition, which falls under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and signal processing (cs.SD). The use of neural networks for dimensionality reduction and object recognition is a common topic in these sub-categories, making them the most likely choices.
